docs.abstract: An inquiry into the killing of Mr. Garner in 2014 ended on Friday after the testimony of a dozen witnesses. Here are five takeaways.
docs.snippet: An inquiry into the killing of Mr. Garner in 2014 ended on Friday after the testimony of a dozen witnesses. Here are five takeaways.
docs.lead_paragraph: The death of Eric Garner has reverberated with unanswered questions and fresh developments over the seven years since a New York police officer placed him in a banned chokehold.

headline.main: Eric Garner’s Mother Wanted Answers for His Death. She Isn’t Satisfied.
headline.print_headline: Garner’s Mother Wanted Answers on His Death. She Isn’t Satisfied.

docs.abstract: Marcus Arbery, Ahmaud Arbery’s father, said that what he had seen in the courtroom was “devastating.”
docs.snippet: Marcus Arbery, Ahmaud Arbery’s father, said that what he had seen in the courtroom was “devastating.”
docs.lead_paragraph: BRUNSWICK, Ga. — As the jury began deliberations Tuesday in the trial over the killing of Ahmaud Arbery, local leaders and out-of-town supporters of the Arbery family said that they were anxious, but held out hope that the defendants would be convicted of at least some charges.

headline.main: The Arbery family and friends say they are anxious but hopeful of guilty verdicts.

docs.abstract: Prosecutors and defense lawyers for the three men accused of murdering Ahmaud Arbery made their final pitches to the jury before deliberations begin. Here is a look at their key arguments.
docs.snippet: Prosecutors and defense lawyers for the three men accused of murdering Ahmaud Arbery made their final pitches to the jury before deliberations begin. Here is a look at their key arguments.
docs.lead_paragraph: The two sides in the trial of the three men accused of murdering Ahmaud Arbery made their closing statements on Monday. Prosecutors will hold off making their rebuttal to the defense arguments until Tuesday morning, after the jury told the judge that they wanted to go home for the night. The judge also said the jury would be relocated to interior rooms in the courthouse so they would not hear the chants of demonstrators outside the courthouse.

headline.main: Here are three takeaways from the lawyers’ closing arguments.

docs.abstract: Around the country, local elections suggested that voters were rejecting the most sweeping calls to reinvent law enforcement.
docs.snippet: Around the country, local elections suggested that voters were rejecting the most sweeping calls to reinvent law enforcement.
docs.lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS — After a Minneapolis police officer murdered George Floyd last year, protesters marched across the country demanding sweeping change to law enforcement. But given the opportunity Tuesday to dismantle their city’s troubled Police Department and replace it with something new, Minneapolis voters said no.

headline.main: ‘We Need Policemen’: Even in Liberal Cities, Voters Reject Scaled-Back Policing
headline.print_headline: Given Chance to Reinvent Policing, Minneapolis Opts for What It Knows

byline.original: By Mitch Smith and Tim Arango

docs.abstract: The lawyers represent Travis McMichael, who fatally shot Mr. Arbery, and his father. The lawyer for the third defendant deferred his opening statement until later in the trial.
docs.snippet: The lawyers represent Travis McMichael, who fatally shot Mr. Arbery, and his father. The lawyer for the third defendant deferred his opening statement until later in the trial.
docs.lead_paragraph: In an opening statement on Friday, the lawyer for Travis McMichael, the man who shot and killed Ahmaud Arbery, painted his client as a man who felt a “duty” to protect his neighborhood, and who had reason to believe that Mr. Arbery had committed a burglary — giving him the right, under Georgia law, to carry out a citizen’s arrest.

headline.main: Defense lawyers portray the fatal shooting of Ahmaud Arbery as self-defense.

byline.original: By Richard Fausset and Tariro Mzezewa

docs.abstract: Readers express relief. One calls it the “only rational and equitable verdict.” Also: A Covid Thanksgiving, and one in prison; children and grief.
docs.snippet: Readers express relief. One calls it the “only rational and equitable verdict.” Also: A Covid Thanksgiving, and one in prison; children and grief.

headline.main: ‘Justice Was Served’: Guilty Verdicts in the Ahmaud Arbery Case

docs.abstract: In closing arguments on Monday, prosecutors also raised a racial motive for why the three white men accused of murdering Ahmaud Arbery began chasing him.
docs.snippet: In closing arguments on Monday, prosecutors also raised a racial motive for why the three white men accused of murdering Ahmaud Arbery began chasing him.
docs.lead_paragraph: BRUNSWICK, Ga. — Prosecutors and defense lawyers made their closing arguments in the case of the fatal shooting of Ahmaud Arbery on Monday, raising the question, barely voiced during the trial, of whether race had been an issue.

headline.main: Lawyers Clash Over Whether Pursuit of Arbery Was Justified
headline.print_headline: Prosecutor Raises Racial Motive in Arbery Killing Trial

byline.original: By Richard Fausset, Tariro Mzezewa and Rick Rojas

docs.abstract: The mayoral race was shaped by Mr. Floyd’s death at the hands of a police officer and the debate about whether to replace the city’s Police Department.
docs.snippet: The mayoral race was shaped by Mr. Floyd’s death at the hands of a police officer and the debate about whether to replace the city’s Police Department.
docs.lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS — Mayor Jacob Frey, a Democrat who led Minneapolis when a police officer murdered George Floyd and the city was overwhelmed by rioting last year, was elected to a second term, The Associated Press projected on Wednesday. Mr. Frey also had opposed efforts to abolish or replace the local police force.

headline.main: Jacob Frey, who oversaw Minneapolis when George Floyd was murdered, wins a second term as mayor.

docs.abstract: The three men charged with killing Ahmaud Arbery were found guilty of murder. We explore how the prosecution secured this verdict from a mostly white jury.

docs.lead_paragraph: Supporters of the Arbery family who had gathered outside the courthouse in Brunswick, Ga., during closing arguments in the trial on Monday said that they were anxious but optimistic that the jury would find the three defendants guilty of murder.
